{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a statutory Delay Repay scheme for all public transport",
        "additional_details": "There are many instances where buses simply don't ran, meaning a once-every-10-minute route can end up running only once per half an hour, causing major inconvenience such as missing connections onto other transport (despite leaving a long waiting gap), and missing appointments. We believe in situations like this passengers should be entitled to compensation.",
        "background": "Enforce legislation for all public transport providers, such as public buses to have a delay repay and compensation scheme, similar to those for train companies, in order to compensate customers for any major delays due to the fault of the provider.",
